Latest completed work (single-building type-deficit guardrail fix)
- Fixed remaining spillover where large off-profile room types could still appear as cross-building SF fillers in Planner Copilot options.
- Tightened baseline fill logic in `fillScenarioCandidatesToBaseline`:
  - Final SF top-up pass now only considers room types that exist in the baseline type mix.
- Added explicit baseline type-deficit gating:
  - New helper computes normalized baseline type deficits from current candidate selections.
  - Cross-building classroom/specialized exceptions are now allowed only when that exact normalized type is still in deficit.
  - Same deficit gating applied when building `allowedInventory` for strict single-building refill.
- Result:
  - Prevents cross-building out-of-profile “big SF” picks (like Public Performance / Assembly) from being kept solely to hit SF.
  - Keeps single-building intent aligned with baseline room-type needs.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed.
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`).
